{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/primary-key-in-sql","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"primary-key---sql\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#primary-key---sql\" aria-label=\"primary key   sql permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>PRIMARY-KEY - SQL</h1>\n<p>A primary key is a field in a table which uniquely identifies each row/record in a database table. Primary keys must contain unique values.\nA primary key column cannot have NULL values.</p>\n<p>A table can have only one primary key, which may consist of single or multiple fields.\nWhen multiple fields are used as a primary key, they are called a composite key.</p>\n<p>If a table has a primary key defined on any field(s), then you cannot have two records having the same value of that field(s).</p>\n<p>To define PRIMARY KEY in SQL:-</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">  CASE 1:-When making the table\n  syntax-\n    CREATE TABLE STUDENTS(\n       ROLL_NO INT             NOT NULL,\n       NAME VARCHAR (20)     NOT NULL,\n       AGE  INT              NOT NULL,   \n       PRIMARY KEY (ROLL_NO)\n    );\n\n  CASE 2:-When there is an existing table in which there is no primary key and you  want to add primary key\n  syntax -\n    (write the following command)\n    ALTER TABLE STUDENTS ADD PRIMARY KEY (ROLL_NO);\n\n  CASE 3 :- For defining a PRIMARY KEY constraint on multiple columns\n  syntax -\n    CREATE TABLE STUDENTS(\n     ROLL_NO   INT              NOT NULL,\n     NAME VARCHAR (20)     NOT NULL,\n     AGE  INT              NOT NULL,\n     PHONE_NO INT (10)      \n     PRIMARY KEY (ROLL_NO,PHONE_NO)\n  );</code></pre></div>\n<p>To delete a PRIMARY KEY :-</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">  APPLICABLE FOR ALL CASES:-\n  syntax -\n     (You can clear the primary key constraints from the table with the syntax given below)\n     ALTER TABLE STUDENTS DROP PRIMARY KEY ;</code></pre></div>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"PRIMARY-KEY - SQL A primary key is a field in a table which uniquely identifies each row/record in a database table. Primary keys must…","frontmatter":{"title":"PRIMARY KEY IN SQL","date":"2020-10-31 17:44:52 +0100","categories":["databases"],"tags":["Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key"],"description":null,"keywords":"Primary_key,implementation,Composite_key","author":"Shivani Verma","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/ec3a3984e81d7268d9fed36d749e0122/02521/databases.png","srcSet":"/static/ec3a3984e81d7268d9fed36d749e0122/02521/databases.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/primary-key-in-sql","date":"2020-10-31T16:44:52.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/primary-key-in-sql","nexttitle":"Localization and Internationalization","nextslug":"/localization-and-internationalization","prevtitle":"JavaScript Array.sort() Method","prevslug":"/javascript-arraysort-method","tagList":["java","interface","callbacks","asynchronus calls","python","pandas","abstraction","OOP","Class","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","co